ADMINLEVEL IMMORTALS
----------

   Technically according to DBAT's heirarchy Implementors are the highest
ranking of officials working for the MUD. Along with admins a ranger of
rankings are listed in this file detaling exactly what immortals are and the
meanings of their particular rankings. 

   @GImmplementors@w - Usually restricted to owners of the MUD. Said owners do
not necessarily own all the assets of DBAT, but are in fact imbued with the
power to make major decisions toward the direction of the MUD in most every
area. In a dispute between owners Iovan has final say, and in particular final
say regarding what is done with his code. 

   @GAdministrators@w - These are the seconds in command to the Implementors, and
have final say over most general things unless overruled by an Implementor. 
This is the highest rank most immortals can usually achieve, as achieving
Implementor status requires a great deal of trust and a vacancy in the
Implementor ranks.

   @GVice Admins@w - These immortals can make general decisions within their
respective fields as long as they are not overruled by a higher ranked
immortal. Administrators and Implementors should issue directives to Vice
Admins delegating duties to them as necessary. Good Vice Admins will have a
keen grasp of current MUD sentiments among both the immortals and player base,
and should provide accurate updates to their superiors regarding anything of
note in regard to said sentiments.

   @GHigh Enforcers@w - These immortals have been given the responsibility of
making sure the rules are followed by players and immortals alike. In
particular High Enforcers are in charge of all lesser enforcers and have final
say in rules arbitration unless overruled by a superior. In the event of
immortal rule breaking High Enforcers should contact every superior with the
same report to prevent a coverup from occuring.

   @GFirst Class Enforcer@w - These immortals focus mostly on enforcing the rules
of the mud, and have had enough positive history as an immortal and experience
of at least four months. Generally speaking First Class Enforcers should take
care of most rules arbitrations and only seek a superior if required. Players
that experience a First Class Enforcer that is not applying the rules
appropriately may petition a superior ranked IMM.

   @GEnforcers@w - The catchall rank for the lowest immortals regardless of their
main job. All immortals are tasked with enforcing the rules if they are the
only ones available to do so, but in general this rank of immortals should
observe how their superiors perform the task prior to being assigned rules
enforcement as their priority role. Enforcers are to enforce the rules as
necessary regardless, but if a superior is present they should be notified with
the problem first, and if that superior wishes to delegate it to the enforcer
or there is an understanding prior to do so on a particular issue then that is
fine.

