ALIAS ALIASES
@c------------------@n
@nUsage: @Galias [alias name] [command]@n

@nAn alias is a single command used to represent one or more other commands. The ALIAS command is used to manipulate your character's aliases.  Type ALIAS alone to see a list of your currently defined aliases.@n

@n>alias

@nType ALIAS <alias name> <command> to create a new alias.  The alias name must be one word.  The command can be any string.  Aliases can not be nested or used recursively.  Any command may be overridden by an alias (other than the ALIAS command itself, 


f course).

@n>alias gbb get bread bag
@n>alias gac get all corpse

@nType ALIAS <alias-name> to delete an alias that has already been defined.

@n>alias gbb

@nA semicolon ("
") can be used to define multiple actions to be taken with a single alias.

@n> alias eat get bread bag
@n eat bread

   @nNote that the 'eat' contained within the eat alias is interpreted as the
MUD's internal eat command aliases may not be nested or used recursively. The
variables $1, $2, ... $9 may be used to represent arguments given with an
alias. @nExamples:


@n>alias killem cast 'fireball' $1
 cast 'harm' $2
@n>alias helpem cast 'heal' $1
 cast 'bless' $1
 cast 'armor' $1

@nThe special variable $* represents the entire input line after an alias:
@n>alias tr tell rasmussen $*
@n>tr hi there, how are you today?
@nYou tell Rasmussen, 'hi there, how are you today?'

@RIf you save the MUD instance you are in when the alias is made, your character aliases will be saved.@n
