EXPERIENCE XP
----------

   Whenever you kill an NPC or a player, or spar with one, you earn experience
points. When enough experience points are earned you can go to your sensei or
another trainer and 'gain' a level. 

   The amount of experience an NPC gives will depend on its type (animal or
humanoid), its race (saiyan, human, dragon, android, etc. ), and its skillset
(such as Roshi skills). Common humanoid NPCs will give the least experience as
they are technically the easiest enemy to defeat. Androids, Bioandroids,
Majins, Dragons, and Saiyan NPCs all have a bonus to their experience reward.

   Finally you can gain additional experience from an NPC defeated if they
happen to have helped another NPC you had been fighting. The interrupting NPC
will get a 4-5% boost to their experience reward. 

   Additionally there are some items that can affect positively or negatively
your experience gained. One such object is the spar booster found within the
rpp menu. 

EXP gained from mobs is now dependant on how many mobs are in a room at the
time of death. 

1-10 gives the normal ammount of EXP
10-15 reduces EXP by 25%
15-20 reduces EXP by 40%
20-30 reduces EXP by 60%
30+   reduces EXP by 80%

See also - help group, help score, help levels
