GUNS
----------

   Guns are technological weapons that shoot things. Whether bullets, energy,
or whatever else we can think of for a weapon. While weapons were not overly
effective in DBZ you will find that they can be here on DBAT. This respects
the wide variety of technology that can be imagined and incorporated into the
game. Below the damage table for gun tiers is listed.

Tier 1: 50 base damage
Tier 2: 200 base damage
Tier 3: 750 base damage
Tier 4: 2,000 base damage
Tier 5: 7,500 base damage

   Gun damage is then further modified by your stats. If your gun skill is 100
or higher then the base damage is multiplied by 2 and added to the original
base amount. If your gun skill is above 50 then the base amount is increased
by 50%. The damage then is multiplied by your agility stat. That number is
then finally multiplied by your character level after it has been divided by 5.

Example: Agility - 100, Gun Skill - 100, Gun of Tier 2, Character level 40
Base Damage 200 + (200 * 2) = 600
600 * 100 = 6,000
6,000 * (40 / 5) = 48,000 dmg (before defenses are calculated)

   Finally if the total damage would exceed 40% of your current max powerlevel
then it will be capped at that amount instead.

   In order to shoot a gun you must have enough zenni on hand. It costs 1
zenni per shot for tier 1, 2 for tier 2, 4 for tier 3, 6 for tier 4, and 12 for
tier 5.

See also - help attack
