LIFEFORCE
----------

   Life Force is the amount of life your character still has in them. The way
it works is as long as you have Life Force left you have a good chance to
regain PL every few seconds while fighting. What you regain will be a portion
of your Life Force pool (seen on the score sheet. ) Life Force total is
determined by 50% of the max Ki and max Stamina of the character in question
(added together. )

   It will not rise when you transform, but will only be maxed out if you have
slept for at least one regen tick. Resting will refill 15% of your max
lifeforce per tick rested. Either sleeping or resting will ONLY refill
lifeforce if you did not heal to full @RPOWERLEVEL@n for that tick. Advanced
cooking meals will fill up lifeforce as well. 

   The amount of PL refilled is equal to 5% of the max life force that
character would have if they slept. This would be 50% of max Ki plus 50% of
max Stamina. 

   Now if a player is hit with a fatal non-sparring attack and has life force
enough left to weather the remaining damage (after substracting your remaining
PL) then you will cling to life, and recover a small amount of your PL at that
moment. The amount recovered is either 5% of your Life Force maximum, if you
have the LF for it after the damage has been calculated, or your level x 100
(example: level 50 x 100 = 5,000 PL). When your Life Force runs out, then you
die.
   
   The life command can be used to set the percentage of your optimal PL that
you want your Life Force to kick in at. Zero will set it off completely. 
This gives you complete control over how your LIfe Force works for you. 
   
Syntax@Y: @ylife (0 - 99)@n
   
