SET
----------
Usage: set [ file | player ] <character> <field> <value>

SET is an extremely powerful command, capable of setting dozens of aspects of characters, both players and 
mobiles.

SET PLAYER forces set to look for a player and not a mobile; useful for players with names such as 'guard'.

SET FILE lets you change players who are not logged on.  If you use SET FILE on a player who IS logged on, your 
change will be lost.  If you wish to set a player who is in the game but is linkless, use set twice -- once with 
the FILE argument, and once without -- to make sure that the change takes.

